# Coding Practice & Google Workspace Collaboration – Project Report

## Overview

This project focused on improving coding skills and learning how to use online collaboration tools effectively. It included completing a coding challenge on a practice platform and creating a Google Form for digital literacy awareness.

## Platforms Used

For coding practice, I used **HackerRank**, where I created an account and completed a beginner-level challenge. This helped me understand basic programming concepts and improve my problem-solving skills.

For collaboration, I used **Google Forms** as part of Google Workspace to create a “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” with five questions, including multiple-choice and short-answer types.

## Work Done

On HackerRank, I successfully completed a beginner challenge, which gave me hands-on experience in coding and logical thinking. I also earned a score/badge, which reflects my progress.

In Google Forms, I designed a quiz to spread awareness about digital literacy among my batchmates. The form collects responses automatically, and the linked Google Sheet helps in analyzing the answers easily.

## Learning Outcome

This project helped me understand the importance of regular coding practice and how platforms like HackerRank can strengthen programming skills. Additionally, I learned how to create and manage online forms for collaboration and data collection.

## Future Use

In the future, I will continue solving coding problems to improve my skills and prepare for placements. I will also use Google Forms and Sheets for academic surveys, quizzes, and collaborative projects, making my work more efficient and organized.
